Part I - Prosper Loan Dataset¶

by Aisha Lawal¶

Introduction¶

Introduce the dataset

This prosper load dataset contains customer data from a loan company named prosper. The dataset has 113,937 observations(loans) with 81 variables. Some of the features include: TotalCreditLinespast7years, LoanStatus, BorrowerAPR, LenderYield, EstimatedReturn, and more

#categorizing loans based on "completed and defaulted"
cat = (loan_df['LoanStatus'] == 'Completed') | (loan_df['LoanStatus'] == 'Chargedoff') | (loan_df['LoanStatus'] == 'Defaulted')
loan_df = loan_df[cat]

def change(row):
    if row['LoanStatus'] == 'Chargedoff':
        return 'Defaulted'
    else:
        return row['LoanStatus']
    
loan_df['LoanStatus'] = loan_df.apply(change, axis=1)
